dataIdInfo.idPurp:
Wisconsin Statewide Zoning Layer Version 2.0.0 (V2.0.0)
The layer was created as a part of the final deliverable to the V2 Statewide Parcel Map Initiative, and is the first public release of Wisconsin statewide zoning data.
See http://www.doa.state.wi.us/Divisions/Intergovernmental-Relations/Land-Information-Program/Statewide-Parcel-Map-Initiative/ for more information on this project.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This file was aggregated as part of the final deliverable for the Version 2 Statewide Parcel Map Database Project (V2). This feature class represents a comprehensive, spatially referenced collection of zoning geometries as recognized by County Governments within the State of Wisconsin (the feature class is aggregated from county level data and represents zoning that is administered by the county). This record describes the GENERAL zoning layer. Additional zoning features are included in the data download: AIRPORT, FARMLAND, FLOODPLAIN, & SHORELAND.See the V2 Project homepage for more detail on the parameters for how data was prepared and submitted to this project: http://www.sco.wisc.edu/images/stories/publications/V2/Submission/.Schema documentation can be found within this feature class as GIS metadata and here: http://www.sco.wisc.edu/images/stories/publications/V2/V2_Wisconsin_Statewide_Parcels_Schema_Documentation.pdf.Change log, and known issues: can be found here: http://www.sco.wisc.edu/images/stories/publications/V2/V2_Wisconsin_Statewide_Zoning_Change_Log.pdf.The Web Service URL in this record displays the "GENERAL" zoning layer only. Visit here for a comprehensive list of Service URLs: http://mapservices.legis.wisconsin.gov/arcgis/rest/services/WLIP_V2

dataLineage.statement: This layer is the result of aggregation procedures implemented over parcel and tax roll data provided by Wisconsin's 72 counties. Counties that administer this zoning type in a GIS format have submitted their zoning data for inclusion in this layer.

- The name of the county contributing the county-administered only zoning data. - Spaces and periods are permitted in county names in the JURISDICTION field.

The class name for the zoning feature. Class names included here are unrestricted and subject to their jurisdictional context. Zoning class values may vary by name or by definition across jurisdictions. See the DESCRIPTION or LINK fields for further detail about the definition of the given zoning class.

Contains a description for the class name of the zoning feature given within the ZONINGCLASS. This field is optional and may not be populated for all features. If this value is <Null>, see the LINK field for further details defining the zoning class.

A web link (URL) to a valid webpage or web document that contains authoritative/official descriptions of the given feature’s zoning class that is annotated within the ZONINGCLASS field. Following this link will bring you to the appropriate document for describing the zoning class annotated within the ZONINGCLASS field. If this field's value is <Null>, see the DESCRIPTION field for further details defining the zoning class.
